This paper deals with Bayesian reinforcement learning in self-interested multi-agent environments. The paper proposes a general framework for integrating parametric models and model priors to produce a fine-grained and compact representation of the other agent's behavior. This work involves machine learning, artificial intelligence, and robotics, which are covered by the sub-categories cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MA, cs.RO, and cs.SY.
